  m_text: 'Ashpit : The ashpit is the chamber located directly beneath the grate
    in a boiler or furnace. It collects ash and unburnt fuel that falls through the
    grate during combustion. The ashpit also allows air to flow upward through the
    grate to support the burning of fuel.'
