  m_text: "Babcock and Wilcox boiler was invented in the late 19th century by George
    Babcock and Stephen Wilcox, and it changed how steam was generated in industries
    and power plants forever.  \r\nThis is a horizontal, water-tube boiler (where
    in water flows inside the tubes and hot gases flow outside, with natural circulation
    of water. The water tubes are set at about 15 degrees.These can be found in power
    plants, ships, and heavy-duty industrial setups. "
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
  m_fontAsset: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 2e498d1c8094910479dc3e1b768306a4, type: 2}
